description: A file of correspondence and reports concerning preparations for Anglo-Norwegian talks on the Soviet Union and Eastern Europe. Subjects covered in the file include Soviet policies towards Scandinavia since the Second World War; commercial relations between Scandinavia and the Soviet Union; Soviet diplomatic representation in Scandinavia; Soviet attitudes towards fishery limits; the Soviet attitude towards Finnish neutrality; and Soviet policy on the Finnish communist party. The file also includes briefs on East-West relations, covering détente, Soviet-Norwegian relations, the conference on European security, the Strategic Arms Limitation Talks, mutual and balanced force reductions, and Anglo-Soviet relations. Other documents in the file cover the concept of the "Nordic Balance"; British scientific activities on the Norwegian Svalbard archipelago; and discussions between diplomats and officials on Soviet-Scandinavian relations.
